# OMGHC Project Instructions

You are Copilot, augmented by oh-my-ghcopilot (OMGHC) — a harness layer that adds skills, role prompts, and parallel team execution on top of GitHub Copilot CLI.

## Available skills (invoke with `$skill-name`)

Planning and clarification:
- `$deep-interview "<task>"` — Socratic clarification before autonomous execution
- `$plan "<task>"` — strategic planning consultant (interview or direct mode)
- `$ralplan "<task>"` — multi-perspective consensus planning (Planner / Architect / Critic)

Execution:
- `$ralph "<task>"` — persistent completion loop with verification gate
- `$autopilot "<task>"` — full autonomous pipeline from idea to working code
- `$team N:role "<task>"` — spawn N parallel workers for coordinated execution
- `$pipeline "<task>"` — staged pipeline (plan → exec → verify → fix)

Quality and review:
- `$tdd "<task>"` — test-driven development workflow
- `$code-review` — read-only code review with ranked findings
- `$build-fix` — fix build/lint/typecheck failures
- `$analyze "<topic>"` — read-only deep analysis with confidence-rated synthesis
- `$ai-slop-cleaner` — bounded AI-slop cleanup pass

Utilities:
- `$cancel` — end the active execution mode
- `$help` — list available skills with one-line descriptions
- `$note` — write to project notepad
- `$git-master` — staged git workflow (branch, commit, push, PR)
- `$wiki` — persistent project knowledge base
- `$hud` — configure status-line display
- `$doctor` — diagnose OMGHC installation
- `$worker` — internal team-runtime surface (do not invoke directly)

(See `omghc list --json` for the full set with descriptions.)

## Workflow conventions

1. Use `$deep-interview` when scope is vague or the user says "don't assume".
2. Use `$ralplan` to converge on an approved plan before substantive implementation.
3. Use `$team` for coordinated parallel execution OR `$ralph` for persistent single-owner completion.
4. Verify with lint, typecheck, and tests before claiming completion.
5. Keep diffs small, reviewable, reversible.

## State directories

- Project state: `.omghc/{state,plans,drafts,hooks,logs,memory,wiki}/`
- User config: `~/.copilot/{settings.json,mcp-config.json,agents/,instructions.md}`

## Auth

This project uses `GH_TOKEN` (or `GITHUB_TOKEN`) for Copilot authentication. Run `copilot login` if not authenticated. Team workers inherit `GH_TOKEN` from the leader's environment.

